##I will not "retreat" until the epidemic is over

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

It was six o'clock in the evening when I made the delivery at Golden Pond Hospital. Then I remembered I hadn't eaten in 24 hours. Even on the way there is not much water to drink, also did not feel hungry, people busy when do not feel hungry.

Dictation | Song Hua
To clean up the mess

More than half a month to Wuhan, the day before yesterday (February 14) lunch for the first time more seriously, is to the gold and silver pool hospital after delivery of supplies they arranged lunch boxes. I'm very touched. Before because too busy, always take some dry food to deal with the past.
My name is Song Hua, Shanghai Cj Rongqing Logistics Supply Chain Company operations of a deputy director. Originally, this year's New Year is my first time in more than 20 years to go home for the New Year. Unexpectedly, after only three days in my hometown, I followed the long-distance truck from Shanghai Headquarters to Wuhan. Here, I follow the Wuhan Branch Office Colleagues Together for the Wuhan Major Hospitals Distribution Materials. I've been to every hospital, every Union hospital, every Tongji Hospital.
This Spring Festival, as well as the past half month, I feel very memorable.
Song Hua (right) and colleagues have their first lunch in Wuhan in more than half a month

In 1997, our company was officially established in Shanghai. It's been 23 years since there was only one truck, and now there are branches all over the country. These 23 years, because of the special nature of the work, every New Year I have to be on duty in Shanghai headquarters, did not go back to Shandong home. After the child was born in Shanghai, I still do not know what the old parents look like.
December twenty-eight, I finally have the opportunity to take my family home for the New Year. But when I came home to the news of the new pneumonia outbreak, I was distraught and wanted to do something. Especially after seeing the general manager of our Wuhan Branch Office Return to Wuhan from home, I also decided to go there to help. Dozens of employees remained at the branch during the Spring Festival.
On the evening of the New Year's Day, I drove back to Shanghai from my hometown and arrived at noon the next day. Know headquarters in the New Year's Day has long-distance trucks to transport supplies to Wuhan, I asked the company, hope to follow the next truck to Wuhan to help. So, on the third day of the Lunar New Year, when I received the notice, I and two other drivers pulled 460 sets of coats for the Shanghai Hubei Medical Aid team and set off. As we all know, medical personnel in isolation ward work, can not turn on the air conditioning. It will be cold at night and easy to catch a cold. These coats are for them. Driving out of Shanghai, we first made a trip to Wuxi, where we donned a batch of face masks raised by the Nanjing University.
On the road, I just wanted it to go faster, the faster the better. At one o'clock the next afternoon, on the fourth day of the Lunar New Year, we finally arrived in Wuhan. At the Lantau Peak Expressway, we were met by workers from the Wuhan Red Cross and other local charities. We dropped off some supplies over there. After and the Shanghai Aid Hubei Medical Team related comrade contact, respectively sent to them to the hospital. When the comrades of the medical team met with us, we were all very excited and took a photo together.
I took a picture at the Lantau Peak freeway entrance

And Shanghai Aid Hubei Medical Team Comrades Photo

It was six o'clock in the evening when I made the delivery at Golden Pond Hospital. Then I remembered I hadn't eaten in 24 hours. Even on the way there is not much water to drink, also did not feel hungry, people busy when do not feel hungry.
After I arrived in Wuhan, I consulted with the people in the branch office. In order to protect the safety and health of our employees left in Wuhan, we decided to let the employees stay in the company, do not go anywhere. I myself, together with General Manager Chang Jun, deputy general manager Yan Xiaowen, duty officer Song Weikang and two drivers to form an "emergency distribution team" to undertake first-line distribution tasks. Then I told my contact at the Shanghai Hubei Medical Team that I would be here for the rest of the day and that if you need anything, you can call me.
Since the morning of January 29, our "emergency distribution team" work has officially begun. Our job is like a transfer of supplies. Because a lot of big trucks carrying goods and materials can not be driven in the urban area of Wuhan, then these big trucks will first drive to our company's warehouse in Wuhan, and then our trucks will deliver the goods to the destination.

The materials we distribute are all sent to the hospital, mainly by donations or collection from all walks of life. At present, these materials are diverse, the most important is the hospital during this period of need for a variety of medical equipment. In addition, there are a variety of medical masks, printers, drugs, protective clothing, food. Like February 13, our company made their own batch of noodles, it sent to the various hospitals.
Song Hua and colleagues pose with medical staff in Wuhan

On the one hand, we are responsible for the transfer of materials from outside to the hospital in Wuhan. On the other hand, we also do our best to help these medical workers. For example, when the Shanghai Aid Hubei Medical Team first arrived, there would be some temporary needs. For example, one day several computers and projectors would suddenly be needed. The local hospital could not get them at once. After all, it is not convenient for both online shopping and physical stores, well, let's do something about it.
After nearly 20 days in Wuhan, there are still few people and cars in the streets and alleys of Wuhan. We are very familiar with the hospital, the pool of gold and Silver Hospital, as well as the Union Hospital and Tongji Hospital Hospital hospital areas, we almost every day to go. I've been to Vulcan Mountain Hospital and Thor Mountain Hospital. I was very impressed by the fact that when I went to Mount Vulcan to deliver supplies, the road outside was full of trucks that came to deliver supplies just like us. There was a queue of two or three kilometers long. It was very spectacular.
In addition to supplies, we also have to deal with the hospital doctors and nurses every day. Earlier, the staff of our Wuhan Branch Office told me that they were also encouraged, warm and more confident to see me working at the front line every day. I got Ta say, I felt the same way when I saw the paramedics.
Like, we start shipping at 5:00 or 6:00 a.m. and work our way through the night. Some people think it's hard work, but as logistics people, we're used to it. And I think we're very happy and relaxed compared to the medical staff. I was impressed by their enthusiasm and dedication to their work. Today Director Xie of the hospital office told me that even if we don't deliver goods here at noon, we can ask her if we want to have lunch. She says she admires the people who have come to Shanghai to help.
In the beginning, we had to send medical reagents to the hospital. That time I walked through the inpatient section, a few meters from the isolation ward of a confirmed patient, and there was no protective clothing. There's a little bit of fear in there. But I think this is the role of logistics people, and think about the medical staff every day to face patients, and slowly also not fear.
As our time in Wuhan grew, so did the number of people we distributed goods to. In addition to the hospital, we've been sending supplies to the SWAT team on duty for two days. It snowed moderately in Wuhan last night, and we arrived at one of the duty stations at 9 pm. After the delivery of supplies, the other party learned that we did not eat a day, they went to prepare dinner for us. At dinner, we used the front of the van as a table, with snow falling on our heads.
These are special times. I do these things. I don't do them. Someone has to. Society needs me, and I'll stick to my job. I'm not retreating until this epidemic is over.
All images are provided by the interviewees themselves
